<h3 class="ex1">
	<p>
		I have to reinstall RVM/Ruby/Rails everytime i open the terminal.
	</p>
</h3>
<h4 class="ex2">
	<p>
	when I open a new terminal, rvm,ruby and/or rails is no longer installed. Place these two lines of code into your "bash.rc" file inside your home folder/directory<br><br>

export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/.rvm/bin # Add RVM to PATH for scripting<br>
[[ -s "$HOME/.rvm/scripts/rvm" ]] && source "$HOME/.rvm/scripts/rvm"<br><br>

Once you have placed the two lines above into bash.rc reinstall ruby,rails and rvm and open a new terminal and type<br>
$ ruby -v <br>
$ rails -v<br>
$ rvm -v
	</p>
</h4>



<h3 class="ex1">
	<p>
	If the bundle isnt installing properly or you get an error with installing certain gems.check your ruby,rails and rvm versions by typing. <br>
	</p>
</h3>
<h4 class="ex2">
	<p>
	$ rvm -v <br>
	$ rails -v <br>
	$ ruby -v<br><br> 

	If they do not show their versions, try installing the one without a version and then try <br><br>
	$ gem install bundler<br>
	$ bundle install<br>
	</p>
</h4>


<h3 class="ex1">
	<p>
	I cannot log into MySQL as ROOT.
	</p>
</h3>
<h4 class="ex2">
	<p>
	Open up your file browser and go to your project folder you have made. then navigate to the folder called "config" this folder will have a file inside that you may have already copied over from before. called Database.yml" inside there is a section that says username and passwords under development,test and production. change this to the desired password and click save. the default should be:<br><br>

	  username: root <br>
	  password: password <br><br>

If the password section is empty, it should be the password you set. If it isn't change the empty password field to what you want, and save. Go to the terminal and try logging in again.
	</p> 
</h4>


